OL,4,Cresuscitate' notice of the wrong
OL,5,Cpatient
OL,7,FThe inquest heard that the patient
OL,8,Fwhose notes were confused for Pat's
OL,9,Fwas a 90-year-old man.
OL,11,F"Unfortunately, tragically and
OL,12,Fcatastrophically these were not Pat's
OL,13,Frecords; they belonged to an entirely
OL,14,Fdifferent patient who was male and in
OL,15,Fhis 90s; characteristics which Pat
OL,16,Fvery clearly did not share," Ms Bisset
OL,17,Fsaid.
OL,19,F"It was quickly realised that a DNR
OL,20,Fwas not in place however, tragically,
OL,21,Fit was too late."
